  <programme start="20260328035500 +0000" stop="20260328044500 +0000" channel="lovenaturehd.unifitv">
    <title lang="en">Wild Rockies</title>
    <desc lang="en">For a great many species, the structures of group living are the most important for survival. Although social living is integral to many of the animals that call the Rocky Mountains home, no two species organize their society in the same way. Even among closely related species there can be drastic differences in social structure; communication, hierarchy, mating, and diet are all inextricably informed by specific environmental and genetic adaptations for group survival.</desc>
    <category lang="en">Wildlife</category>
    <episode-num system="xmltv_ns">0.4.</episode-num>
